main event: On February 9, 1959, residents of Washington, D.C. reported seeing a bright, elliptical-shaped light moving rapidly and silently across the night sky, which was later classified as an unidentified flying object (UFO) by the Air Force's Project Blue Book investigation team.
interesting points: The UFO sighting involved several residents of Washington, D.C. and was described as a bright, elliptical-shaped light moving rapidly and silently across the night sky.
A local businessman was able to photograph the object using a 35mm camera, and the attached photograph shows the object as it appeared in the sky.
The Aerospace Technical Intelligence Center concluded that the image in the photograph was that of an aircraft, based on their evaluation of the negative.
The provided documents include requests for analysis of the UFO film and original negatives for further evaluation.
Despite thorough investigations, the object could not be identified, and the case remains open and under investigation by Project Blue Book.
witnesses: several residents of Washington, D.C., a local businessman
